	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65483512">Followed a course in college about real time operating systems for critical hardware. The professor pleaded strongly against C and C++ because statistics showed more mistakes were made in these languages. (rust probably did not exist back then). The example that I remember was "if (a = 5) ". It compiles and runs. But it is a typo that is not flagged. Of course, I summarize a few lectures in a few sentences. She treated this in detail. <br>
Whenever I throw this in a discussion, it usually goes in the "Good prog</div>
	</div>

